<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,1401,2037]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1653,1677]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jones &amp; Clayton" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[324,619,1653,1677]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Leptochryseus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuwaitense">
<emphasis box="[324,619,1653,1677]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Leptochryseus kuwaitense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[981,1063,1653,1677]" name="Kuwait" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D." box="[1110,1385,1653,1677]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="183 - 199" refId="ref48716" refString="Jones, D. A. &amp; Clayton, D. (1983) The systematics and ecology of crabs belonging to the genera Cleistostoma and Paracleistostoma on Kuwait mudflats. Crustaceana, 45 (2), 183 - 199." type="journal article" year="1983">Jones &amp; Clayton (1983)</bibRefCitation>
and assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="De Haan, 1833" authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1833" box="[398,725,1689,1713]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Cleistostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[398,544,1689,1713]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Cleistostoma</emphasis>
De Haan, 1833
</taxonomicName>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Khayat, J. A. &amp; Jones, D. A." box="[808,1107,1689,1713]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="797 - 813" refId="ref44562" refString="Al-Khayat, J. A. &amp; Jones, D. A. (1996) Two new genera, Manningis and Leptochryseus (Decapoda: Camptandriinae), and descriptions of the first zoea of six Brachyurans from the Arabian Gulf. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 16 (4), 797 - 813." type="journal article" year="1996">Al-Khayat &amp; Jones (1996)</bibRefCitation>
introduced a new monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Al-Khayat &amp; Jones, 1996" authorityName="Al-Khayat &amp; Jones" authorityYear="1996" box="[225,681,1725,1749]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Leptochryseus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[225,387,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Leptochryseus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Al-Khayat, J. A. &amp; Jones, D. A." box="[396,681,1725,1749]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="797 - 813" refId="ref44562" refString="Al-Khayat, J. A. &amp; Jones, D. A. (1996) Two new genera, Manningis and Leptochryseus (Decapoda: Camptandriinae), and descriptions of the first zoea of six Brachyurans from the Arabian Gulf. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 16 (4), 797 - 813." type="journal article" year="1996">Al-Khayat &amp; Jones,1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and transferred 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jones &amp; Clayton" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[874,1032,1725,1749]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Leptochryseus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuwaitense">
<emphasis box="[874,893,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[908,1032,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">kuwaitense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the new genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F." box="[1252,1436,1725,1750]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref51230" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F. (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of extant brachyuran crabs of the world. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 17, 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="2008">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[1294,1345,1725,1749]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
. (2008)
</bibRefCitation>
did not recognize the genus as a valid taxon and synonymized it with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1833" box="[948,1094,1761,1785]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Cleistostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[948,1094,1761,1785]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Cleistostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L. &amp; Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D." box="[1223,1406,1761,1786]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref51169" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Rahayu, D. L. &amp; Naser, M. D. (2009) The Campatndriidae of Iraq, with description of a new genus and notes on Leptochryseus Al-khayat &amp; Jones, 1996 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Zootaxa, 2312, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[1265,1316,1761,1785]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
in their work on the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[358,537,1797,1821]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camptandriidae</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[578,623,1798,1821]" name="Iraq" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Iraq</collectingCountry>
compared 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jones &amp; Clayton" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[751,907,1797,1821]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Leptochryseus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuwaitense">
<emphasis box="[751,766,1798,1821]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[783,907,1797,1821]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">kuwaitense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[975,1208,1797,1821]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Nasima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dotilliformis">
<emphasis box="[975,1208,1797,1821]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Nasima dotilliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(two species which were originally included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1833" box="[473,619,1833,1857]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Cleistostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[473,619,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Cleistostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in detail. They came to the result that the two species, regarding the carapace morphology and adult sexual dimorphism, are different enough to be placed into two different genera. However, they still were not convinced in recognizing these genera as they share many important characters e.g. similar male abdomen, similar first male gonopod and relatively similar ambulatory legs. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jones &amp; Clayton" baseAuthorityYear="1983" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Leptochryseus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuwaitense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Leptochryseus kuwaitense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the northern Persian Gulf. The record of the species from western Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1330,1398,1977,2001]" name="Oman" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Oman</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ismail, N. S. &amp; Ahmed, M. A. E." box="[151,420,2013,2037]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="155 - 161" refId="ref48475" refString="Ismail, N. S. &amp; Ahmed, M. A. E. (1993) Macrobenthic invertebrates of mangrove, Avicennia marina (Forskal), and of intertidal flats of Khor Kalba, U. A. E., Gulf of Oman. In: Lieth, H. &amp; Al Masoom, A.: Towards the rational use of high salinity tolerant plants, Vol. 1. Tasks for Vegetation Sciences, 27 (1), 155 - 161." type="journal article" year="1993">Ismail &amp; Ahmed (1993)</bibRefCitation>
is a misidentification of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[700,871,2013,2037]" class="Malacostraca" family="Camptandriidae" genus="Nasima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dotilliformis">
<emphasis box="[700,871,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">N. dotilliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[930,1051,2013,2037]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
